org.anchoranalysis.annotation.io.bean

Class AnnotatorStrategy

  • Object
    • AnchorBean<AnnotatorStrategy>
      • AnnotatorStrategy
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SinglePathStrategy

    public abstract class AnnotatorStrategy
extends AnchorBean<AnnotatorStrategy>
    How an input is associated with annotations on the file-system, and how this is presented visually.

    This class gives instructions on how to present the annotations process visually.

    Author:
    Owen Feehan

      • pathFor

        public abstract Path pathFor(ProvidesStackInput input)
                      throws OperationFailedException
        The path to where an annotation file for a particular input would be located.

        If the annotation is stored on multiple files, this refers to the principle file that must be unique.

        Parameters:
        input - the input to find an annotation file for.
        Returns:
        the path to where the annotation would be expected to be.
        Throws:
        OperationFailedException - if the path cannot be successfully determined.

      • annotationLabelFor

        public abstract Optional<String> annotationLabelFor(ProvidesStackInput input,
                                                    Logger logger)
                                             throws OperationFailedException
        A human-friendly textual description of the annotation, or Optional.empty() if no label is available.
        Parameters:
        input - the input to find an annotation label for.
        logger - where to write informative messages to, and and any non-fatal errors (fatal errors are throw as exceptions).
        Returns:
        the label, if available.
        Throws:
        OperationFailedException - if a label cannot be successfully determined.

      • weightWidthDescription

        public abstract int weightWidthDescription()
        The degree as to how lengthy the labels from annotationLabelFor(ProvidesStackInput, Logger) can be.

        The higher the number, the lengthier annotationLabelFor(ProvidesStackInput, Logger) can be.

        Returns:
        the weight.
